https://leetcode.com/problems/contiguous-array/description/

QUESTION:
Input: nums = [0,1,1,1,1,1,0,0,0]
Output: 6
Explanation: [1,1,1,0,0,0] is the longest contiguous subarray with equal number of 0 and 1.

SOLUTION:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)use a map to store the rsum values
2)store rsum with index.
3)
Initialize:
1) map.put(0, -1) → handles case when subarray from index 0 has equal 0s & 1s
2) Traverse array:
    If 1 → rsum += 1
    If 0 → rsum -= 1
3) For each rsum:
    If not seen before → store index
    If seen before:
4)That means subarray between previous index and current index has sum = 0
    Length = i - previousIndex
    Update max

If the same prefix sum appears again, it means the elements in between balanced out (equal 0s and 1s).
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int findMaxLength(int[] nums) {
        if(nums==null || nums.length<=1)return 0;
        HashMap<Integer,Integer>map=new HashMap<>();
        int rsum=0;
        int max=0;
        map.put(0,-1);
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[i]==1)rsum+=1;
            if(nums[i]==0)rsum-=1;
            if(!map.containsKey(rsum)){
                map.put(rsum,i);
            }else{
                max=Math.max(max,i-map.get(rsum));
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
}

